Spain,[h] also the Kingdom of Spain,[a][i] is a country in Southern and
Western Europe with territories in North Africa.[j] Featuring the southernmost
point of continental Europe, it is the largest country in Southern Europe
and the fourth-most populous European Union member state. Spanning across
the majority of the Iberian Peninsula, its territory also includes the Canary
Islands, in the Eastern Atlantic Ocean, the Balearic Islands, in the Western
Mediterranean Sea, and the autonomous cities of Ceuta and Melilla.